				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Denekamp</placeName> <date>der 28 July</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">My very dear uncle&#58;</p>
			<p>Although it is well a long time since I have<lb/> written you&#44; and it is not so well from me&#44;<lb/> that say myself&#59; but on the other side<lb/> <sic>thougt</sic> always I receive every month a book<lb/> from you&#59; and then I know also that you are<lb/> in good health&#59; the same I can tell you from<lb/> my side and hope that our <hi rend="underline">Father</hi> may give you<lb/> health yet many years <add>Hebrew</add>......<add>&#63;</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Also I have read in the last book that<lb/> aunt is dead in the month of <date>May</date>&#44; it is well<lb/> good that God has taken her from this earth&#59;<lb/> in her live was nothing here&#59; then a man<lb/> how cannot see is very unhappy.  My mother<lb/> says now I shall well receive a letter in<lb/> short time from your uncle&#44; because the<lb/> aunt is dead.  My dear uncle&#44; if you write<lb/> my&#44; to write a <sic>lettle</sic> greater than in the<lb/> last letter from you&#44; are any words who I<lb/> cannot read&#44; but therefore you must not be<lb/> angry on me.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Last week we have read every day in the<lb/> newspaper that <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> and the other<lb/> towns in <placeName>Pennsylvania</placeName> should be declared in<lb/> state of seige&#44; which make us very sorrowful<lb/> <sic>becauseyou</sic>&#59; and my mother and father says<lb/> that you go to an other land where the war<lb/> does not rule&#44; than where the war so is&#44; one</p>
